Anthrax, Namibia
----------------
Information received on [and dated] 12 Nov 2018 from Dr Adrianatus Florentius Maseke, chief veterinary officer, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Water and Forestry, Windhoek, Namibia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 25 Oct 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 1 Nov 2018
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 13 Feb 2018
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (3)
Outbreak 1: Omiriu, Opuwo, Sesfontein, Kunene
Date of start of the outbreak: 25 Oct 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Goats / 537 / 25 / 23 / 2 / -

Outbreak 2: Oruhona, Opuwo, Sesfontein, Kunene
Date of start of the outbreak: 25 Oct 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 100 / 2 / 2 / - / -

Outbreak 3: Bwabwata, Rundu, Omega, Kavango East
Date of start of the outbreak: 25 Oct 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: natural park
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
African buffalo (Cape buffalo): _Syncerus caffer_ (Bovidae) - / 25 / 25 / - / -

Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 3
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of
Goats / 537 / 25 / 23 / 2
Cattle / 100 / 2 / 2 / -
African buffalo (Cape buffalo): _Syncerus caffer_ (Bovidae) / 25 / 25 / - / -
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages], expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Goats / 4.7 / 4.3 / 92 / **
Cattle / 2 / 2 / 100 / **
African buffalo (Cape buffalo): _Syncerus caffer_ (Bovidae) ** / ** / 100 / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive; persistent spores in the environment from last year's (2017) outbreak at Bwatata [Bwabwata] National Park

Control measures:
Measures applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; official destruction of animal products; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; selective killing and disposal; disinfection; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory) / African buffalo (Cape buffalo) / bacteriological examination 1 Nov 2018 / Positive
Central Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory) / Goats / bacteriological examination / 1 Nov 2018 / Positive
Central veterinary laboratory (National laboratory) / Cattle / bacteriological examination / 1 Nov 2018 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above. Kunene is in north west Namibia, and Kavango East is between Angola & Botswana in the north east.

